@startuml lf-mmi
' Lattice-Free MMI training: the numerator graph (correct transcript) and the
' denominator graph (phone loop + LM covering all hypotheses) each score the
' acoustic posteriors via forward-backward; the MMI objective is their difference,
' warmed up / stabilized by cross-entropy regularization. Matches
' build_numerator_graph / build_denominator_graph / lfmmi_loss / LfMmiConfig in
' src/training/lfmmi.rs (Povey et al. 2016).
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #BF360C
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.4
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 12
  FontColor #102027
  BorderColor #E65100
}

title <b>Lattice-Free MMI</b>\n<size:11>L_MMI = −( log P_num(x) − log P_den(x) ) ;  warm-started with cross-entropy (xent_regularize)</size>

rectangle "<b>Acoustic posteriors</b>\nlog P(pdf∣frame)  [T × num_pdfs]" as X #E1BEE7

rectangle "<b>Numerator graph</b>\ncorrect transcript · HMM topology\nbuild_numerator_graph" as NUM #FFE0B2
rectangle "<b>Denominator graph</b>\nphone loop + phone-LM (all hypotheses)\nbuild_denominator_graph" as DEN #FFCC80

X -down-> NUM : forward-backward
X -down-> DEN : forward-backward

rectangle "<b>log P_num(x)</b>\nscore of the reference path" as PNUM #C8E6C9
rectangle "<b>log P_den(x)</b>\nlog Σ_y P(y∣x)  (leaky-HMM smoothed)" as PDEN #C8E6C9

NUM -down-> PNUM
DEN -down-> PDEN

rectangle "<b>MMI objective</b>\nL = −(log P_num − log P_den)" as MMI #FFB74D
PNUM -down-> MMI
PDEN -down-> MMI

rectangle "<b>Warmup / regularization</b>\n+ xent_regularize · L_xent\n+ l2_regularize · ∥out∥²\n+ leaky_hmm_coefficient" as REG #FFCDD2
MMI -down-> REG : interpolate

rectangle "<b>Gradients</b>\n∂L / ∂(acoustic scores)\nLfMmiGradients" as GRAD #ECEFF1
REG -down-> GRAD : backprop

note right of DEN
  The denominator covers <i>all</i> competing word/phone
  sequences, so the lattice never has to be generated
  explicitly — hence "lattice-free" (Povey et al. 2016).
end note

note right of REG
  Early in training the MMI signal is noisy; interpolating
  with frame-level cross-entropy (the warmup term) keeps
  optimization stable until the model is well-aligned.
end note
@enduml
